#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.93"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.93:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.93:0.2"
msgid "10. Loṇakapallavagga "
msgstr "10. A Lump of Salt "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.93:0.3"
msgid "93. Pavivekasutta "
msgstr "93. Seclusion "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.93:1.1"
msgid "“Tīṇimāni, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā pavivekāni paññāpenti. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, wanderers who follow other paths advocate three kinds of seclusion. "

msgctxt "an3.93:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.93:1.3"
msgid "Cīvarapavivekaṃ, piṇḍapātapavivekaṃ, senāsanapavivekaṃ. "
msgstr "Seclusion in robes, alms-food, and lodgings. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.241, sc2
#. VAR: tirīṭānipi → tirīṭakānipi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: ajinampi → ajinānipi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.93:2.1"
msgid "Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā cīvarapavivekasmiṃ paññāpenti, sāṇānipi dhārenti, masāṇānipi dhārenti, chavadussānipi dhārenti, paṃsukūlānipi dhārenti, tirīṭānipi dhārenti, ajinampi dhārenti, ajinakkhipampi dhārenti, kusacīrampi dhārenti, vākacīrampi dhārenti, phalakacīrampi dhārenti, kesakambalampi dhārenti, vālakambalampi dhārenti, ulūkapakkhikampi dhārenti. "
msgstr "Wanderers who follow other paths advocate this kind of seclusion in robes. They wear robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings. "

msgctxt "an3.93:2.2"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā cīvarapavivekasmiṃ paññāpenti. "
msgstr "This is what wanderers who follow other paths advocate for seclusion in robes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.93:3.1"
msgid "Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā piṇḍapātapavivekasmiṃ paññāpenti. "
msgstr "Wanderers who follow other paths advocate this kind of seclusion in alms-food. "

msgctxt "an3.93:3.2"
msgid "Sākabhakkhāpi honti, sāmākabhakkhāpi honti, nīvārabhakkhāpi honti, daddulabhakkhāpi honti, haṭabhakkhāpi honti, kaṇabhakkhāpi honti, ācāmabhakkhāpi honti, piññākabhakkhāpi honti, tiṇabhakkhāpi honti, gomayabhakkhāpi honti, vanamūlaphalāhārā yāpenti pavattaphalabhojī. "
msgstr "They eat herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. They survive on forest roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit. "

msgctxt "an3.93:3.3"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā piṇḍapātapavivekasmiṃ paññāpenti. "
msgstr "This is what the wanderers who follow other paths advocate for seclusion in alms-food. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: rukkhamūlaṃ susānaṃ → rukkhamūlaṃ bhusāgāraṃ susānaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: bhusāgāraṃ → suññāgāraṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.93:4.1"
msgid "Tatridaṃ, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā senāsanapavivekasmiṃ paññāpenti araññaṃ rukkhamūlaṃ susānaṃ vanapatthaṃ abbhokāsaṃ palālapuñjaṃ bhusāgāraṃ. "
msgstr "Wanderers who follow other paths advocate this kind of seclusion in lodgings. They stay in a wilderness, at the root of a tree, in a charnel ground, a forest, the open air, a heap of straw, or a threshing-hut. "

msgctxt "an3.93:4.2"
msgid "Idaṃ kho, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā senāsanapavivekasmiṃ paññāpenti. "
msgstr "This is what wanderers who follow other paths advocate for seclusion in lodgings. "

msgctxt "an3.93:4.3"
msgid "Imāni kho, bhikkhave, tīṇi aññatitthiyā paribbājakā pavivekāni paññāpenti. "
msgstr "These are the three kinds of seclusion that wanderers who follow other paths advocate. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.93:5.1"
msgid "Tīṇi kho panimāni, bhikkhave, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye bhikkhuno pavivekāni. "
msgstr "In this teaching and training, there are three kinds of seclusion for a mendicant. "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā ca hoti, dussīlyañcassa pahīnaṃ hoti, tena ca vivitto hoti; "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant is ethical, giving up unethical conduct, being secluded from it. "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.4"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, micchādiṭṭhi cassa pahīnā hoti, tāya ca vivitto hoti; "
msgstr "They have right view, giving up wrong view, being secluded from it. "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.5"
msgid "khīṇāsavo ca hoti, āsavā cassa pahīnā honti, tehi ca vivitto hoti. "
msgstr "They’ve ended defilements, giving up defilements, being secluded from them. "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.6"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti, dussīlyañcassa pahīnaṃ hoti, tena ca vivitto hoti; "
msgstr "When a mendicant has these three kinds of seclusion, "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.7"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, micchādiṭṭhi cassa pahīnā hoti, tāya ca vivitto hoti; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.8"
msgid "khīṇāsavo ca hoti, āsavā cassa pahīnā honti, tehi ca vivitto hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.93:5.9"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aggappatto sārappatto suddho sāre patiṭṭhito’. "
msgstr "they’re called a mendicant who has reached the peak and the pith, being pure and grounded in the essential. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.242, sc6
msgctxt "an3.93:6.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kassakassa gahapatissa sampannaṃ sālikkhettaṃ. "
msgstr "When a farmer’s rice field is ripe, "

#. VAR: sīghaṃ sīghaṃ → sīghasīghaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.93:6.2"
msgid "Tamenaṃ kassako gahapati sīghaṃ sīghaṃ lavāpeyya. "
msgstr "they’d have the rice cut swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.3"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ lavāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ saṅgharāpeyya. "
msgstr "gathered swiftly, "

#. VAR: ubbahāpeyya → ubbāhāpeyya (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "an3.93:6.4"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ saṅgharāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ ubbahāpeyya. "
msgstr "transported swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.5"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ ubbahāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ puñjaṃ kārāpeyya. "
msgstr "made into heaps swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.6"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ puñjaṃ kārāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ maddāpeyya. "
msgstr "threshed swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.7"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ maddāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ palālāni uddharāpeyya. "
msgstr "the straw and chaff removed swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.8"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ palālāni uddharāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ bhusikaṃ uddharāpeyya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.9"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ bhusikaṃ uddharāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ opunāpeyya. "
msgstr "winnowed swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.10"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ opunāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ atiharāpeyya. "
msgstr "brought over swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.11"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ atiharāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ koṭṭāpeyya. "
msgstr "threshed swiftly, "

msgctxt "an3.93:6.12"
msgid "Sīghaṃ sīghaṃ koṭṭāpetvā sīghaṃ sīghaṃ thusāni uddharāpeyya. "
msgstr "and have the husks removed swiftly. "

#. VAR: Evamassu → evassu (mr)
msgctxt "an3.93:6.13"
msgid "Evamassu tāni, bhikkhave, kassakassa gahapatissa dhaññāni aggappattāni sārappattāni suddhāni sāre patiṭṭhitāni. "
msgstr "In this way that farmer’s crop would reach the peak and the pith, being pure and consisting only of what is essential. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "an3.93:7.1"
msgid "Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yato bhikkhu sīlavā ca hoti, dussīlyañcassa pahīnaṃ hoti, tena ca vivitto hoti; "
msgstr "In the same way, when a mendicant is ethical, giving up unethical conduct, being secluded from it; "

msgctxt "an3.93:7.2"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiko ca hoti, micchādiṭṭhi cassa pahīnā hoti, tāya ca vivitto hoti; "
msgstr "when they have right view, giving up wrong view, being secluded from it; "

msgctxt "an3.93:7.3"
msgid "khīṇāsavo ca hoti, āsavā cassa pahīnā honti, tehi ca vivitto hoti. "
msgstr "when they’ve ended defilements, giving up defilements, being secluded from them: "

msgctxt "an3.93:7.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ‘bhikkhu aggappatto sārappatto suddho sāre patiṭṭhito’”ti. "
msgstr "they’re called a mendicant who has reached the peak and the pith, being pure and grounded in the essential.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.93:7.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
